reviews.review_text: Great show! This was the first Greek run for me being an east coaster and boy was it great. This show had the breakout of "Keep On Growing" as well as the dusting off of two other classic songs: "Stagger Lee" and "Comes A Time" (one of my favorite Jerry ballads). Finally this show had a Morning Dew to open the 2nd set. That hadn't happened since the early 70's. What a great time. Seems like only yesterday....

7:03pm PST, 8/6/2017 I wrote a review and posted it along with a recording of the show to my FB page. Feel free to check it out. The name is William Menzel. This being my second Greek treat. Summer '84 my first. Driving the pilgrimage from Boston. The mecca, Berkeley, CA and temple being 3days of the GD @ the Greek Theatre. 
 I'm from the East coast like you. & already had been on almost every east coast spring, fall & summer. I feel as if I finally graduated from Grateful Dead U. after making it to the Greek Theatre.
